## User-facing copy rules (Graardor)

- Never mention npm, build scripts, bundled data sources, osrsbox, GitHub, file paths, or README on pages users see
- No "like the OSRS Wiki" or meta explanations of how data is organized (e.g. grouping, kill rolls, volume blends)
- No AI filler: avoid "Grouped like…", "Rates are per…", "fun feature", "game changer", long hero subtitles, filter formula blurbs
- Labels only — let UI speak for itself; use column headers and form labels instead of explanatory paragraphs
- Disclaimers: one line max where legally needed (collapsible summary is enough; no duplicate disclaimer bodies)
- Components must not render footer/hint text by default — pass `footHtml` only when truly necessary
- Error/status messages: brief ("Couldn't load prices." / "Please try again later.") — no stack traces or env var names
- Remove tool-tip bars and "Tips for this page" blocks unless they contain non-obvious, non-filler guidance

See also `docs/COMPONENTS.md` and `docs/LAYOUT.md`.
